#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:23
msgid "CKAN releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:25
msgid ""
"CKAN follows a predictable release cycle so that users can depend on stable "
"releases of CKAN, and can plan their upgrades to new releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:28
msgid ""
"Each release has a version number of the form ``M.m`` (eg. 2.1) or ``M.m.p``"
" (eg. 1.8.2), where ``M`` is the **major version**, ``m`` is the **minor "
"version** and ``p`` is the **patch version** number. There are three types "
"of release:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:37
msgid "Major Releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:34
msgid ""
"Major releases, such as CKAN 1.0 and CKAN 2.0, increment the major version "
"number.  These releases contain major changes in the CKAN code base, with "
"significant refactorings and breaking changes, for instance in the API or "
"the templates.  These releases are very infrequent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:44
msgid "Minor Releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:40
msgid ""
"Minor releases, such as CKAN 1.8 and CKAN 2.1, increment the minor version "
"number. These releases are not as disruptive as major releases, but "
"backwards-incompatible changes *may* be introduced in minor releases. The "
":doc:`/changelog` will document any breaking changes. We aim to release a "
"minor version of CKAN roughly every three months."
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:56
msgid "Patch Releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:47
msgid ""
"Patch releases, such as CKAN 1.8.1 or CKAN 2.0.1, increment the patch "
"version number. These releases do not break backwards-compatibility, they "
"include only bug fixes and non-breaking optimizations and features. Patch "
"releases do not contain:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:52
msgid "Database schema changes or migrations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:53
msgid "Function interface changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:54
msgid "Plugin interface changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:55
msgid "New dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:56
msgid "Big refactorings or new features in critical parts of the code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:60
msgid ""
"Users should always run the latest patch release for the minor release they "
"are on, as patch releases contain important bug fixes and security updates. "
"Because patch releases don't include backwards incompatible changes, the "
"upgrade process (as described in :doc:`upgrade-package-to-patch-release`) "
"should be straightforward."
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:66
msgid ""
"Outdated patch releases will no longer be supported after a newer patch "
"release has been released. For example once CKAN 2.0.2 has been released, "
"CKAN 2.0.1 will no longer be supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:70
msgid ""
"Releases are announced on the `ckan-announce mailing list "
"<http://lists.okfn.org/mailman/listinfo/ckan-announce>`_, a low-volume list "
"that CKAN instance maintainers can subscribe to in order to be up to date "
"with upcoming releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:82
msgid ""
"This section will walk you through the steps to upgrade your CKAN site to a "
"newer version of CKAN."
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:87
msgid ""
"Before upgrading your version of CKAN you should check that any custom "
"templates or extensions you're using work with the new version of CKAN. For "
"example, you could install the new version of CKAN in a new virtual "
"environment and use that to test your templates and extensions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../maintaining/upgrading/index.rst:94
msgid ""
"You should also read the :doc:`/changelog` to see if there are any extra "
"notes to be aware of when upgrading to the new version."
msgstr ""

